## Security controls implemented

- Dedicated least-privilege Samba user (`backupuser`, no login shell, no SSH access)
- Password-protected Restic repository, password file locked to `600` permissions
- ext4 filesystem with standard Unix permission enforcement on the backup volume
- Weekly automated integrity verification (`restic check`)
- SIEM alerting on backup failure via custom Wazuh rules (rule ID 100200, level 7)
- A tested, verified restore — not just a backup that's assumed to work

## Recovery objectives

- **RPO (Recovery Point Objective):** 24 hours — backups run nightly via cron
- **RTO (Recovery Time Objective):** under 1 hour — verified via a real restore test in [docs/PHASE5-verify-restore.md](docs/PHASE5-verify-restore.md)

