## Lessons learned

See [docs/INCIDENT-REPORT.md](docs/INCIDENT-REPORT.md) for the real troubleshooting history on this build — including a root-owned Docker volume blocking rsync, a Restic password file permissions mismatch that silently broke automated backups, and a Wazuh agent event-queue flood caused by an overly broad log wildcard. These are documented as deliberate evidence of practical troubleshooting, not hidden as failures.

## Status

Server-side backup lab (HDD mount → rsync → Samba → Restic → verify → Wazuh alerting) is complete and tested end-to-end. Windows client-side automated backup (Task Scheduler + robocopy pushing to the Samba share) is in progress and will be documented separately once verified.

